    "biography": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Thyra Blackhand</strong> is a former Chainwarden Sergeant who deserted her post when the dead began moving. She leads approximately 30 civilians behind fortified barricades at the Greyfen Holdfast&mdash;a ruined village turned refugee camp on the road between the Interior Belt and the Titan's Stair pass.</p><p>Thyra is practical, suspicious, and hard-bitten. She doesn't trust institutions anymore&mdash;she deserted the Chainwardens because the system abandoned the people it was supposed to protect. She has nothing to lose and is ready to die defending what little she has.</p>",
      "director": "<section class=\"secret\"><p>Thyra is the Beat 8 negotiation encounter at Greyfen Holdfast. She controls passage through the most direct road to Titan's Stair.</p><p>She responds to <strong>pragmatism</strong> and <strong>hope</strong>, not authority or threats. Invoking the King's name costs Patience&mdash;she deserted; she doesn't trust the crown. Threatening her triggers immediate hostility (8+ armed refugees, sharpened stakes, barricades). If Kaelen reveals her ember-mark, several refugees weep, one elderly man kneels, and Thyra opens the gate.</p><p>If the PCs help her materially (tactics against draugr, fire as weapon, reinforcing barricades), she survives the approaching draugr column and leads her people to Hrafnborg, becoming a valuable military contact in Act 2&mdash;'a sergeant who knows how to fight the dead.'</p><p>If the PCs fail or ignore her, the holdfast falls. They may find the aftermath later.</p></section>",
